1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:01,320
Look,

2
00:00:01,760 --> 00:00:03,080
the answer is no.

3
00:00:05,730 --> 00:00:06,930
But why? Give me a reason.

4
00:00:07,240 --> 00:00:08,610
Because I like you, Minato.

5
00:00:13,310 --> 00:00:14,310
Wait.

6
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:17,140
No, that's not what I meant. I misspoke.

7
00:00:17,900 --> 00:00:19,680
It's not that I don't like you...

8
00:00:22,910 --> 00:00:23,910
It's just...

9
00:00:23,990 --> 00:00:24,990
It's okay.

10
00:00:29,060 --> 00:00:30,870
I like you too, so it's fine.

11
00:00:50,830 --> 00:00:52,260
No, don't look so happy!

12
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:58,280
Wait, no.

13
00:00:58,310 --> 00:01:00,310
I was saying that to myself.

14
00:01:01,390 --> 00:01:02,390
Anyway,

15
00:01:02,660 --> 00:01:03,766
it's because we're best friends.

16
00:01:03,790 --> 00:01:06,530
I like you because you're my best friend.

17
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:10,370
But I meant I like you romantically.

18
00:01:14,660 --> 00:01:17,670
- I meant in a romantic way...
- I heard you the first time!

19
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:19,600
What... what is even happening?

20
00:01:20,100 --> 00:01:21,580
This is the first I've heard of this.

21
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:24,440
I told you I wanted to live
together the day I got back.

22
00:01:25,290 --> 00:01:27,100
I thought you just misspoke!

23
00:01:27,580 --> 00:01:28,659
No, you're the one who's wrong here!

24
00:01:28,660 --> 00:01:29,660
Why?

25
00:01:29,850 --> 00:01:30,939
If you like me too, Wataru...

26
00:01:30,940 --> 00:01:31,940
Hold on.

27
00:01:32,430 --> 00:01:33,430
Just... time out.

28
00:01:34,140 --> 00:01:35,500
Let me talk.

29
00:01:36,230 --> 00:01:37,330
Fine.

30
00:01:37,410 --> 00:01:38,510
We can take a time out.

31
00:01:39,460 --> 00:01:40,460
Okay.

32
00:01:43,490 --> 00:01:44,490
Listen.

33
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:47,790
We are each other's absolute best friends.

34
00:01:48,270 --> 00:01:50,030
We can keep this
relationship going forever.

35
00:01:50,170 --> 00:01:50,870
That's so cheesy.

36
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:51,900
Let it be cheesy!

37
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:53,760
Just listen.

38
00:01:54,490 --> 00:01:57,820
We don't need a romance that's
just destined to end eventually.

39
00:02:02,350 --> 00:02:04,960
You're my best friend, Minato.

40
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:07,220
I want us to stay that way.

41
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:09,620
Same here. I want that too.

42
00:02:11,090 --> 00:02:12,090
But...

43
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:16,820
I also want to live with
you as my best friend.

44
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:20,740
I thought we were on a time out!

45
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:22,090
Time outs have to end sometime.

46
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:24,150
Look... anyway.

47
00:02:25,030 --> 00:02:26,590
I want to keep things the way they are.

48
00:02:27,470 --> 00:02:28,600
Just like always.

49
00:02:28,630 --> 00:02:29,450
Being your best friend.

50
00:02:29,451 --> 00:02:30,720
If things don't stay the same,

51
00:02:31,820 --> 00:02:33,340
does that mean we can't live together?

52
00:02:37,470 --> 00:02:38,470
Wataru.

53
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:41,110
Move in with me.

54
00:02:44,620 --> 00:02:45,620
Let's

55
00:02:46,270 --> 00:02:47,270
live together.

56
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,600
"Countdown To Yes"

57
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,799
(September 14, 2025)

58
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,860
Did he really mean what he said?

59
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:54,410
"I like you too, so it's fine."

60
00:03:55,210 --> 00:03:57,100
"I meant I like you romantically."

61
00:03:57,450 --> 00:03:59,410
- "I meant in a romantic way..."
- No, no, no, no!

62
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:02,700
(Episode 4)

63
00:04:02,780 --> 00:04:03,780
Because...

64
00:04:04,660 --> 00:04:05,940
Being one-of-a-kind best friends

65
00:04:06,180 --> 00:04:08,450
is way more important
than being boyfriends.

66
00:04:10,780 --> 00:04:12,849
You can forgive a boyfriend for things,

67
00:04:12,850 --> 00:04:14,596
but if a friend did them,
you might not stand it.

68
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:18,050
Meaning, you only overlook things
while the "love filter" is on.

69
00:04:31,340 --> 00:04:33,110
If Minato and I date,

70
00:04:33,180 --> 00:04:34,540
and become a couple,

71
00:04:36,290 --> 00:04:39,060
that means we could eventually break up.

72
00:04:42,090 --> 00:04:43,490
And if that happens,

73
00:04:44,330 --> 00:04:46,790
I'll never be able to see him again.

74
00:04:50,970 --> 00:04:51,970
I really can't do it.

75
00:04:53,690 --> 00:04:54,900
If I lose Minato,

76
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:56,990
I'll have nowhere left to go.

77
00:04:57,770 --> 00:04:59,440
You can always come back here, can't you?

78
00:05:00,350 --> 00:05:01,350
Dad!

79
00:05:02,180 --> 00:05:03,900
Stop jumping into my private conversations.

80
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:05,516
And stop opening my door without knocking.

81
00:05:05,540 --> 00:05:08,410
I've called you for
breakfast like three times.

82
00:05:09,046 --> 00:05:10,046
Oh... sorry.

83
00:05:10,470 --> 00:05:12,550
Your mom's waiting for you downstairs.

84
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,400
Yeah, I'll be right there.

85
00:05:20,780 --> 00:05:21,980
*muffled screaming*

86
00:05:27,370 --> 00:05:28,370
Morning.

87
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,100
Morning...

88
00:05:32,010 --> 00:05:33,800
This is the best. It's top-tier stuff.

89
00:05:34,010 --> 00:05:35,010
Thanks.

90
00:05:35,290 --> 00:05:36,679
- Let's eat.
- Dig in.

91
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,680
Thanks for the food.

92
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:45,690
This is good.

93
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,960
Since it's a long weekend,
do you have any plans?

94
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,880
No, nothing special.

95
00:05:53,950 --> 00:05:54,950
By the way,

96
00:05:55,570 --> 00:05:57,520
Minato's back in town, right?

97
00:05:59,180 --> 00:06:00,180
I guess so.

98
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:01,660
What do you mean, "I guess so"?

99
00:06:01,670 --> 00:06:02,870
Haven't you seen him?

100
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:04,930
Well... yeah, I've seen him.

101
00:06:05,030 --> 00:06:06,030
Hey!

102
00:06:06,060 --> 00:06:08,720
It's not fair if you're the
only one who gets to see him.

103
00:06:08,810 --> 00:06:09,650
Exactly.

104
00:06:09,690 --> 00:06:11,939
Your parents would like to see him too.

105
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:12,940
Right?

106
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:15,050
Minato's busy.

107
00:06:15,670 --> 00:06:17,030
He's a working professional now.

108
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:19,650
Even professionals get days off.

109
00:06:19,930 --> 00:06:22,680
Hey, since he's finally back,

110
00:06:22,930 --> 00:06:24,490
why don't we throw him a welcome party?

111
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:25,760
A welcome party?

112
00:06:25,843 --> 00:06:27,186
Wait, are you guys even listening?

113
00:06:27,210 --> 00:06:28,670
Minato has to work.

114
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,680
Honey,

115
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:31,900
that's a great idea.

116
00:06:32,060 --> 00:06:33,739
- Right?
- Yeah, let's do it.

117
00:06:33,740 --> 00:06:35,900
We can invite Shio-kun and
the others like we used to.

118
00:06:35,930 --> 00:06:37,770
How about a BBQ in the backyard?

119
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:39,690
- I love it!
- Perfect.

120
00:06:39,860 --> 00:06:42,310
We used to do it every year
when they were students.

121
00:06:42,340 --> 00:06:44,889
- I miss those BBQs.
- They were so much fun.

122
00:06:44,890 --> 00:06:47,210
BBQ! BBQ!

123
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:49,300
- BBQ!
- No!

124
00:06:50,110 --> 00:06:51,140
Absolutely not!

125
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,440
What's wrong?

126
00:06:55,550 --> 00:06:56,550
What's gotten into you?

127
00:06:57,210 --> 00:06:57,980
In the past,

128
00:06:57,981 --> 00:07:00,490
you were always the most excited one.

129
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:02,960
Well, yeah, but...

130
00:07:04,910 --> 00:07:06,929
I know you work hard,

131
00:07:06,930 --> 00:07:08,740
but you need to relax sometimes.

132
00:07:09,890 --> 00:07:11,160
Just like the old days,

133
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,300
everyone getting together
and having a good time.

134
00:07:13,570 --> 00:07:17,477
Wait, are you just saying this
because you want to see him?

135
00:07:17,502 --> 00:07:19,360
Don't act like you
don't want to see him too.

136
00:07:19,660 --> 00:07:20,660
You caught me.

137
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:23,650
How long has it been?

138
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:27,450
- Like the old days...
- Two or three years?

139
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:31,099
- Friends...
- No, it's definitely been longer than that.

140
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:32,899
I really want to do this.

141
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:36,080
It'd be so nice to have
everyone over again.

142
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:37,920
Fine, I get it.

143
00:07:38,090 --> 00:07:39,090
Let's do it.

144
00:07:39,140 --> 00:07:41,349
A "just friends" party, like always.

145
00:07:41,350 --> 00:07:42,300
Really?

146
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:43,360
Yay!

147
00:07:46,050 --> 00:07:47,200
BBQ!

148
00:07:47,660 --> 00:07:48,660
BBQ!

149
00:07:49,883 --> 00:07:50,883
Minato is a friend.

150
00:07:51,543 --> 00:07:52,953
Minato is just a friend.

151
00:07:54,670 --> 00:07:55,520
A friend...

152
00:07:55,530 --> 00:07:58,959
Let's make a shopping
list. And check the shed...

153
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:01,160
The grill and everything
should still be in there.

154
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:03,800
And the charcoal...

155
00:08:04,420 --> 00:08:05,700
We'll need to buy more charcoal.

156
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:07,580
Definitely.

157
00:08:08,310 --> 00:08:10,810
Shio-kun's wife is so beautiful.

158
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,750
She's absolutely adorable.

159
00:08:13,690 --> 00:08:16,719
Well, it helps that the
photographer is so talented.

160
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:17,760
Of course.

161
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:20,420
Wataru's the best
photographer in the world.

162
00:08:20,830 --> 00:08:22,579
Ever since he started at the studio,

163
00:08:22,580 --> 00:08:25,599
his skills have gone to a whole new level.

164
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,760
They really have.

165
00:08:26,946 --> 00:08:29,596
Maybe we should have him
take a portrait of us next time?

166
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:30,969
Wait, really?

167
00:08:30,970 --> 00:08:34,149
Mom, Dad, stop it!

168
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:37,520
It's embarrassing when you
brag about me to my friends.

169
00:08:37,580 --> 00:08:39,009
Oh, what's the big deal?

170
00:08:39,010 --> 00:08:40,830
What, are you in your rebellious phase?

171
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:44,219
- A bit late for that, don't you think?
- Just stop.

172
00:08:44,220 --> 00:08:46,970
- Rebellious phase.
- So rebellious.

173
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:48,990
How cute.

174
00:08:58,790 --> 00:09:00,690
"I meant I like you romantically."

175
00:09:06,190 --> 00:09:07,850
Minato, go ahead and eat.

176
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:10,480
Seriously, my parents...

177
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,760
They said this was a welcome party for you,

178
00:09:13,170 --> 00:09:15,720
but they're so busy talking,
they're not even hosting.

179
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:18,570
They're great, though.
Your parents.

180
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:20,320
Huh? What's so great about them?

181
00:09:20,690 --> 00:09:23,800
You can tell how much they love you.

182
00:09:24,810 --> 00:09:26,500
It's really heartwarming.

183
00:09:27,980 --> 00:09:28,980
Minato,

184
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:33,280
you're just enabling them.

185
00:09:33,950 --> 00:09:35,910
Your parents

186
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:38,420
are important to me too.

187
00:09:42,370 --> 00:09:43,370
What's wrong?

188
00:09:43,790 --> 00:09:45,290
Oh, nothing.

189
00:09:46,850 --> 00:09:48,270
This is done.

190
00:09:48,650 --> 00:09:49,650
Wataru, take this over.

191
00:09:50,870 --> 00:09:51,870
Okay.

192
00:09:52,690 --> 00:09:54,780
Wait, you burned it.

193
00:09:55,430 --> 00:09:56,740
It's still edible.

194
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:58,030
No, that's definitely charcoal.

195
00:09:58,650 --> 00:10:00,850
We used to eat stuff like
this in college all the time.

196
00:10:01,290 --> 00:10:02,510
Hey! Don't eat that!

197
00:10:05,010 --> 00:10:06,280
Here, try some.

198
00:10:06,490 --> 00:10:07,710
No... I'm good, really.

199
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:09,960
- It's fine, I'm telling you.
- I said no!

200
00:10:13,060 --> 00:10:14,400
- Oh, it's actually good.
- See?

201
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:20,910
I'm gonna go eat. You
should eat too, Minato.

202
00:10:24,150 --> 00:10:25,736
- That's why you're not popular.
- Just like the old days...

203
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:26,830
Just like the old days...

204
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:30,760
- Welcome back!
- Here, have some burnt bean sprouts.

205
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,859
- Look who's here, Mr. Rebellious.
- Stop calling me that.

206
00:10:32,860 --> 00:10:35,056
- Did Mr. Rebellious burn these?
- Are you still on that?

207
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:36,860
Seriously, give it a rest.

208
00:10:38,530 --> 00:10:39,530
Just eat.

209
00:10:40,010 --> 00:10:41,170
There's plenty more inside.

210
00:10:41,230 --> 00:10:43,150
Want some of the secret sauce on this?

211
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,810
Minato, you're still taking photos?

212
00:10:58,410 --> 00:10:59,410
Yeah.

213
00:10:59,420 --> 00:11:00,439
Well, unlike Wataru,

214
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,610
it's just a hobby for me.

215
00:11:02,340 --> 00:11:05,230
You two are always
taking pictures together.

216
00:11:05,740 --> 00:11:06,740
Are we?

217
00:11:06,741 --> 00:11:07,850
Yeah.

218
00:11:08,140 --> 00:11:11,280
It feels like you have your own world
that no one else can enter.

219
00:11:11,430 --> 00:11:14,239
I mean, why else would you ignore us
and take so many photos?

220
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:14,790
Yeah.

221
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,080
Oh... sorry about that.

222
00:11:16,439 --> 00:11:17,439
No, no, no, no!

223
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:18,920
It's not like that.

224
00:11:18,980 --> 00:11:19,980
Not at all!

225
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,080
- Oh...
- Ah.

226
00:11:21,809 --> 00:11:22,929
Okay, nine minutes,

227
00:11:23,380 --> 00:11:24,380
fifty-nine seconds.

228
00:11:24,940 --> 00:11:26,030
No way!

229
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:28,200
Okay, my turn next!

230
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:29,250
Alright, I'm next.

231
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,200
That's a great smile.

232
00:11:39,110 --> 00:11:40,150
No, stop it!

233
00:11:40,620 --> 00:11:41,620
Cut it out!

234
00:11:49,930 --> 00:11:52,170
What does "like the old days"

235
00:11:52,650 --> 00:11:53,960
even mean for us?

236
00:11:57,390 --> 00:11:58,530
Come on, everyone!

237
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:00,480
Okay, look over here.

238
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:02,160
Ready? I'm taking it.

239
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:03,750
Say cheese!

240
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:05,820
Perfect.

241
00:12:05,940 --> 00:12:06,940
Wataru.

242
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:08,910
On my way here today,

243
00:12:08,970 --> 00:12:10,600
I ran into Moriyama-sensei.

244
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:13,240
He wants us to help out with
the photography club's event.

245
00:12:13,540 --> 00:12:14,990
- When?
- Tomorrow.

246
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:16,970
Tomorrow? That's so sudden.

247
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:18,630
Do you have plans?

248
00:12:18,976 --> 00:12:20,386
No, not really.

249
00:12:21,060 --> 00:12:22,060
Then let's go together.

250
00:12:22,620 --> 00:12:23,620
Just the two of us?

251
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:24,700
Yeah.

252
00:12:25,830 --> 00:12:26,830
The two of us...

253
00:12:28,460 --> 00:12:29,890
Is that a problem?

254
00:12:30,852 --> 00:12:32,502
No, it's not that.

255
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:39,290
Sensei said he hasn't seen you
in forever and wants to catch up.

256
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:47,450
Plus, since you're working at a studio now, he
said the students would be thrilled to have you.

257
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:53,800
Hmm.

258
00:12:53,801 --> 00:12:55,199
Alright, I'll go.

259
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:56,230
Thanks.

260
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:57,800
I'm gonna go help clean up over there.

261
00:13:17,810 --> 00:13:18,810
Morning.

262
00:13:26,790 --> 00:13:28,830
Seriously, I'm so pumped for this.

263
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Oh, wait.

264
00:13:30,220 --> 00:13:31,520
Can I just take one picture?

265
00:13:36,230 --> 00:13:37,990
Doesn't this look amazing?

266
00:13:39,890 --> 00:13:41,830
Athletes always look 20% cooler in photos.

267
00:13:48,230 --> 00:13:48,990
Wataru.

268
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:50,040
Yeah?

269
00:13:51,210 --> 00:13:52,210
It's golden hour.

270
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:55,350
What are you doing?
There are bugs over there.

271
00:14:12,030 --> 00:14:13,030
You're early.

272
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:15,600
Not really.

273
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:18,640
Hmm?

274
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:19,920
Oh.

275
00:14:20,230 --> 00:14:21,230
Never mind.

276
00:14:22,250 --> 00:14:23,250
Okay.

277
00:14:26,110 --> 00:14:27,110
Yokoi.

278
00:14:27,220 --> 00:14:28,320
Nakano.

279
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:30,440
Sensei!

280
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,590
You guys are lifesavers.

281
00:14:33,690 --> 00:14:34,690
Thank you for coming.

282
00:14:34,866 --> 00:14:37,876
Of course. It's nice to be back
at school after all this time.

283
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:40,850
I'm so glad I ran into Yokoi yesterday.

284
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:43,480
You two are still as close as ever, I see.

285
00:14:43,700 --> 00:14:44,700
You think so?

286
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:47,809
This is Wataru in his "grown-up" phase.

287
00:14:47,810 --> 00:14:49,060
Shut up.

288
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:51,810
- You're avoiding eye contact.
- No, I'm not.

289
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:54,400
I'm just keeping you out
of my peripheral vision.

290
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:56,710
What does that even mean?

291
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:58,370
See? You did it again.

292
00:14:58,400 --> 00:14:59,530
Fine, I did it.

293
00:14:59,570 --> 00:15:01,460
- That was a quick confession.
- Is this better?

294
00:15:01,540 --> 00:15:03,540
Why are you so close?

295
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:07,010
You two haven't changed a bit.

296
00:15:08,020 --> 00:15:09,120
It's good to see.

297
00:15:10,780 --> 00:15:12,520
Well, I'll leave it to you.

298
00:15:13,130 --> 00:15:15,080
The students are excited to meet you.

299
00:15:23,410 --> 00:15:25,319
(Session 1: School Photo Shoot) First,
I want you all to think about something.

300
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:27,026
(Guest Speakers: Nakano Wataru,
Yokoi Minato) Before you press the shutter,

301
00:15:27,050 --> 00:15:28,050
are we...

302
00:15:28,450 --> 00:15:30,199
actively "taking" the photo,

303
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,599
or is the photo "taking" us?

304
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:35,100
I want you to really consider that.
Now, everyone, close your eyes.

305
00:15:35,830 --> 00:15:37,200
Take a deep breath.

306
00:15:39,920 --> 00:15:41,240
Okay, open them.

307
00:15:42,580 --> 00:15:43,010
Isn't this one great?

308
00:15:43,011 --> 00:15:44,610
- Oh, that's so cute.
- Right?

309
00:15:57,460 --> 00:15:59,659
Maybe try using this filter?

310
00:15:59,660 --> 00:16:00,660
Thank you.

311
00:16:04,470 --> 00:16:06,800
- Let's try a shot from over here.
- Okay.

312
00:16:13,630 --> 00:16:14,460
How's this?

313
00:16:14,460 --> 00:16:15,460
Oh, wow.

314
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:16,500
That's nice. Yeah.

315
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:17,900
Great.

316
00:16:17,900 --> 00:16:18,900
Let me see.

317
00:16:19,970 --> 00:16:20,970
Hey, this is really good.

318
00:16:21,490 --> 00:16:22,500
You look so cool.

319
00:16:23,660 --> 00:16:27,130
Yeah, the light from that angle is perfect.

320
00:16:27,540 --> 00:16:29,960
Try shooting like this next time.

321
00:16:30,010 --> 00:16:30,470
Okay.

322
00:16:30,471 --> 00:16:32,430
Thank you so much.

323
00:16:39,510 --> 00:16:40,770
The shadows?

324
00:16:41,050 --> 00:16:42,050
That's a good idea.

325
00:16:43,810 --> 00:16:44,810
Yeah.

326
00:16:45,290 --> 00:16:47,490
- Try getting a bit closer.
- Got it.

327
00:16:48,810 --> 00:16:52,800
- I love the photos you take.
- Really? Thanks.

328
00:16:53,340 --> 00:16:54,660
Look at this one. Isn't it great?

329
00:16:55,970 --> 00:16:56,970
Check out mine too.

330
00:16:57,710 --> 00:16:59,660
It's really good, seriously.

331
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,520
How do you get them to look like this?

332
00:17:09,790 --> 00:17:11,600
Should I change the settings for this?

333
00:17:12,260 --> 00:17:13,260
That's not it.

334
00:17:13,420 --> 00:17:14,830
This kind of soft, out-of-focus look

335
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:15,989
is what makes vintage lenses so charming.

336
00:17:15,990 --> 00:17:17,230
That's what I was going to say.

337
00:17:17,350 --> 00:17:19,540
But doesn't that just mean it's blurry?

338
00:17:20,060 --> 00:17:22,790
A photo doesn't have to be
perfectly in focus to be good.

339
00:17:23,900 --> 00:17:25,480
They aren't perfect, but they're warm.

340
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:28,550
That's why I've always
loved your photos, Minato.

341
00:17:33,630 --> 00:17:34,630
Oh.

342
00:17:34,660 --> 00:17:35,450
Are you mad?

343
00:17:35,450 --> 00:17:36,450
Why would I be?

344
00:17:36,890 --> 00:17:38,210
I'm saying I really like them.

345
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:40,710
I could never capture that feeling myself.

346
00:17:41,650 --> 00:17:43,960
But that's what makes
photography interesting.

347
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:54,090
Why does Minato feel so far away right now?

348
00:17:58,210 --> 00:17:59,690
It's like we're back in the old days.

349
00:18:18,780 --> 00:18:20,500
But the one who can't go back

350
00:18:20,940 --> 00:18:21,940
is me.

351
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:30,350
Sensei, thank you for everything.

352
00:18:33,510 --> 00:18:34,510
He called me "Sensei."

353
00:18:35,090 --> 00:18:36,210
That's kind of embarrassing.

354
00:18:40,210 --> 00:18:42,360
You guys did a great
job. It was a huge help.

355
00:18:43,020 --> 00:18:45,040
Here, a little something for your time.

356
00:18:45,060 --> 00:18:47,040
Whoa, this brings back memories.

357
00:18:47,510 --> 00:18:49,156
The drinks from the
cafeteria vending machine.

358
00:18:49,180 --> 00:18:50,700
I can't believe they still have these.

359
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:53,790
A lot of things around
here haven't changed.

360
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:57,100
Well, thanks again for today.

361
00:19:02,790 --> 00:19:03,990
Things that haven't changed...

362
00:19:08,326 --> 00:19:09,326
Wataru?

363
00:19:09,790 --> 00:19:10,790
Oh.

364
00:19:14,950 --> 00:19:16,350
This is nice.

365
00:19:21,460 --> 00:19:23,340
It's really nostalgic.

366
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:24,840
Yeah.

367
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:27,510
Suddenly, I really want
to take some photos.

368
00:19:28,050 --> 00:19:29,050
Me too.

369
00:19:32,990 --> 00:19:34,740
You're a good teacher, Wataru.

370
00:19:35,130 --> 00:19:36,130
You think so?

371
00:19:36,380 --> 00:19:38,260
You always have been.

372
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,366
There you go with the "always" again.

373
00:19:40,390 --> 00:19:42,260
What did I ever teach you?

374
00:19:42,860 --> 00:19:45,220
Back during our last
competition in high school.

375
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,400
(May 17, 2017)
Hmm...

376
00:19:50,350 --> 00:19:52,390
I want to capture a warmer feeling.

377
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:55,730
You're really into it this time.

378
00:19:56,430 --> 00:19:58,350
Well, it's our last competition.

379
00:19:59,790 --> 00:20:01,370
I didn't think you cared about that.

380
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:02,700
I'm actually surprised.

381
00:20:03,730 --> 00:20:05,300
It's not about winning.

382
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:09,440
I want to put everything from our
three years together into these photos.

383
00:20:10,180 --> 00:20:11,460
What are you even talking about?

384
00:20:12,100 --> 00:20:13,560
Over the last three years,

385
00:20:13,770 --> 00:20:15,680
I've learned so much from you.

386
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:17,810
This is like my final project.

387
00:20:24,350 --> 00:20:25,960
The light still isn't right.

388
00:20:28,630 --> 00:20:29,630
In that case,

389
00:20:31,470 --> 00:20:32,670
why don't you try a filter?

390
00:20:33,470 --> 00:20:34,560
A filter?

391
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,490
Look.

392
00:20:37,240 --> 00:20:38,240
Oh, wow.

393
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:39,640
That's amazing.

394
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:40,750
How did you do that?

395
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:49,080
Makes a difference, right?

396
00:20:57,750 --> 00:20:58,750
Yeah.

397
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:22,240
Oh, yeah. I remember that.

398
00:21:23,140 --> 00:21:25,180
That was a fun time.

399
00:21:26,620 --> 00:21:31,220
Even though we both
totally lost that competition.

400
00:21:31,710 --> 00:21:33,760
Didn't you get an honorable mention?

401
00:21:34,330 --> 00:21:35,920
An honorable mention...

402
00:21:37,630 --> 00:21:39,410
That sounds exactly like something I'd get.

403
00:21:41,070 --> 00:21:42,930
We went to the beach after that, didn't we?

404
00:21:43,460 --> 00:21:45,530
Oh, yeah, we did.

405
00:21:46,070 --> 00:21:48,430
You said we needed a change of scenery.

406
00:21:49,320 --> 00:21:51,000
The photos I took at the beach that day...

407
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:52,820
I still love them.

408
00:21:54,970 --> 00:21:56,290
The beach, huh?

409
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:59,220
I haven't been in years.

410
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:01,440
Want to go?

411
00:22:01,670 --> 00:22:02,770
To the beach.

412
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:05,590
To take photos.

413
00:22:06,340 --> 00:22:07,340
Sure.

414
00:22:07,490 --> 00:22:08,490
That sounds great.

415
00:22:08,710 --> 00:22:10,430
I haven't used film in a while.

416
00:22:11,370 --> 00:22:14,400
Let me check...

417
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:17,290
I'm off tomorrow and the day after.

418
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:18,600
So,

419
00:22:20,090 --> 00:22:21,790
come stay over at my place.

420
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:38,050
Stay... over?

421
00:22:45,080 --> 00:22:46,110
(Next Episode)
The beach!

422
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:48,410
Taking photos I love with Wataru.

423
00:22:48,530 --> 00:22:49,830
Eating delicious food.

424
00:22:50,290 --> 00:22:51,290
This is so good.

425
00:22:51,550 --> 00:22:52,980
This really is the best.

426
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:57,040
I really am...

427
00:22:57,080 --> 00:22:59,390
Just listen to a request
from your best friend, Minato.
